<p class="wikiPara">
I'm happy to announce new Weld 1.1.3.Final release.
</p>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> <a href="https://issues.jboss.org/secure/ReleaseNote.jspa?projectId=12310891&amp;version=12316782" target="" class="regularLink">Release notes</a>
</li>
</ul>

<p class="wikiPara">
With this release we finally moved Weld Core Arquillian tests by default to <a href="http://www.jboss.org/as7" target="" class="regularLink">JBoss AS7</a>, making the build easier and faster -- thanks Stuart.
</p>

<p class="wikiPara">
But this of course doesn't mean we forgot about other containers; 
</p>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> it's still fully tested against latest GlassFish (thanks GF guys!), </li>
</ul>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> added new web container tests (Tomcat 7; thanks Matija) and </li>
</ul>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> reduced Jetty config a bit (thanks Geoffrey).</li>
</ul>


<p class="wikiPara">
Other interesting issues or features include:
</p>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> simple <a href="https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WELD-510" target="" class="regularLink">portlet integration</a> - thanks Marko</li>
</ul>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> better conversation handling - thanks <a href="https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WELD-877" target="" class="regularLink">Lincoln</a> and <a href="https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WELD-865" target="" class="regularLink">George</a>; btw, <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/lincolnthree" target="" class="regularLink">LB3</a> I expect more patches from now on ;-)</li>
</ul>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> <a href="https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WELD-966" target="" class="regularLink">resolution by name</a> - thanks Martin</li>
</ul>

<ul class="wikiUnorderedList">
<li class="wikiUnorderedListItem"> Java like <a href="https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WELD-1001" target="" class="regularLink">abstract method handling in decorators</a>- thanks me; since I'm already thanking everyone :-)</li>
</ul>

<br>

<p class="wikiPara">
<a href="https://github.com/weld/core/" target="" class="regularLink">Weld' github master</a> will now be the basis of future 1.2 releases, moving current to branch 1.1.
</p>

<p class="wikiPara">
(since there already is an <q>abandoned</q> 1.1 branch, we'll first move that one to 1.1-legacy)
</p>

<br>

